TY  - JOUR
AB  - Protective tariff was endorsed in 1881 by the American Federation of Labor, followed in 1882 by declaration of neutrality. Beginning in 1906, the Federation has approved requests from affiliated organizations with regard to specific tariff proposals. In 1928 America's Wage Earners Protective Conference was organized.
