TY  - JOUR
AB  - The definition of production in terms of value changes is traced from simple form value to the current four-fold classification of stuff, form, place and time value. It is submitted that these four categories fail to embrace certain value changes which are important in present day economic life. Cases of faulty extension of the classification are analyzed. Finally, it is pointed out that the classification is inadequate for defining production in that it includes only values incorporated in an economic good.
